- (woman screams)

254
00:22:25,078 --> 00:22:27,614
(phone rings)

255
00:22:28,849 --> 00:22:31,218
(footsteps in corridor)

256
00:22:34,888 --> 00:22:37,291
(man speaking Spanish)

257
00:22:44,298 --> 00:22:47,000
(man arguing)

258
00:22:56,176 --> 00:22:58,679
(man shouting)

259
00:23:00,547 --> 00:23:03,050
(banging on wall)

260
00:23:29,943 --> 00:23:32,546
Mom! Mom...

261
00:23:36,283 --> 00:23:39,319
- I told you, it's not a video game!
- Then what is it?

262
00:23:39,319 --> 00:23:41,855
Well, it's not a video game.

263
00:23:42,890 --> 00:23:45,392
(Billy) This one has
a number on it. Does yours?

264
00:23:45,392 --> 00:23:49,563
- No... Oh, wait. Here's one.
- What are you doing? What are you doing?

265
00:23:49,630 --> 00:23:54,001
- Do you have Zoltar?
- No, I told you. I've got Power House...

266
00:23:54,134 --> 00:23:56,436
- We need Zoltar.
- I haven't got it.

267
00:23:56,870 --> 00:23:59,573
-(Billy) This is it.
- They're not gonna have it.

268
00:23:59,573 --> 00:24:02,142
- Can I help you?
- Yes. We would like a list...

269
00:24:02,276 --> 00:24:04,878
- ..of all carnivals and fairs.
- And arcades.

270
00:24:04,978 --> 00:24:07,781
Carnivals and... fairs...

271
00:24:07,915 --> 00:24:10,617
Uh, try Consumer Affairs.
Down the hall - room 111.

272
00:24:10,717 --> 00:24:11,885
Thank you.

273
00:24:12,719 --> 00:24:15,722
Fill this out in triplicate. $5 filing charge.

274
00:24:16,657 --> 00:24:19,660
- See?
- You get it in six weeks.

275
00:24:21,962 --> 00:24:26,567
- Six weeks?
- Sometimes longer, but you could get lucky.

276
00:24:26,900 --> 00:24:29,603
Next, please.

277
00:24:30,504 --> 00:24:31,905
Fill this out.

278
00:24:33,841 --> 00:24:36,910
I'm gonna be thirty years old
for the rest of my life.

279
00:24:36,977 --> 00:24:40,848
Would you come on?
We'll figure something out.

280
00:24:40,848 --> 00:24:44,184
By the way...
you may be older than that! (chuckles)

281
00:24:46,587 --> 00:24:50,224
- So now what?
- I'll come and see you every day after school.

282
00:24:50,324 --> 00:24:53,861
- How?
- I'll tell them I made the basketball team.

283
00:24:53,994 --> 00:24:56,063
- What am I gonna do?
- You can get a job.

284
00:24:56,063 --> 00:24:59,199
- I can't get a job.
- Why? What are you good at?

285
00:24:59,199 --> 00:25:01,301
I don't know. Making spitballs?

286
00:25:01,368 --> 00:25:04,204
- How 'bout a delivery man?
- I don't know how to drive.

287
00:25:04,304 --> 00:25:06,373
Yeah, right.

288
00:25:08,175 --> 00:25:11,712
