289
00:25:11,712 --> 00:25:15,249
- You're not eating your cherry?
- Go ahead.

290
00:25:16,717 --> 00:25:18,819
- Clerical transcriber?
- Billy.

291
00:25:18,886 --> 00:25:20,254
Yeah?

292
00:25:24,224 --> 00:25:28,262
- Gross. Oh, God! Gr... That's gross!
- Check, please.

293
00:25:28,395 --> 00:25:31,098
- Go on.
- Collection agent. Company clerk.

294
00:25:31,198 --> 00:25:36,970
- Computer operator. Construction engineer.
- Computer operator? Read that one.

295
00:25:37,037 --> 00:25:41,108
- Will you quit with your stupid computers?
- Just read it!

296
00:25:41,742 --> 00:25:45,078
- "MacMillan Toys..." Toys!
- Toys!

297
00:25:45,579 --> 00:25:47,181
(both)
Wiggy-wiggy jazz.

298
00:25:47,447 --> 00:25:50,817
- (phone rings)
- MacMillan Toys. May I help you?

299
00:25:50,918 --> 00:25:53,086
- Are these the applications?
- Yes.

300
00:25:53,220 --> 00:25:56,123
OK, OK, what's next? There.

301
00:25:56,223 --> 00:25:59,126
Previous employment.

302
00:25:59,259 --> 00:26:02,196
- Your paper route.
- I don't think I can put that.

303
00:26:02,262 --> 00:26:05,832
- Paper route circulation director?
- Yeah!

304
00:26:09,136 --> 00:26:11,438
What's he got?

305
00:26:14,708 --> 00:26:17,211
Hey, don't worry about it.

306
00:26:17,211 --> 00:26:22,216
- Um... Social Security number?
- 32-17-25.

307
00:26:22,216 --> 00:26:24,785
- What is that?
- My locker combination.

308
00:26:25,118 --> 00:26:27,221
Great.

309
00:26:27,287 --> 00:26:29,289
Mr Baskin?

310
00:26:29,590 --> 00:26:31,592
Mr Baskin?

311
00:26:31,592 --> 00:26:35,963
- Y-yes... Yes.
- The personnel director will see you now.

312
00:26:38,465 --> 00:26:40,868
Uh... your son can wait out here.

313
00:26:41,802 --> 00:26:43,670
(Billy giggles)

314
00:26:43,770 --> 00:26:48,075
OK. Son, you should sit down.
And don't give the lady any trouble, now.

315
00:26:48,141 --> 00:26:50,344
Sure,
Dad.

316
00:26:51,211 --> 00:26:55,349
- This way.
- Don't forget, look 'em in the eye.

317
00:26:56,416 --> 00:26:59,620
(manic clicking of pen)

318
00:27:06,627 --> 00:27:09,630
There's two numbers missing
on your Social Security.

319
00:27:09,763 --> 00:27:12,266
Oh. Uh... 12.

320
00:27:13,934 --> 00:27:16,003
1-2.

321
00:27:19,006 --> 00:27:21,642
It says here you've got four years' experience.

322
00:27:21,708 --> 00:27:24,545
- Yes.
- All on computers?

323
00:27:24,645 --> 00:27:26,713
Yes.

324
00:27:29,983 --> 00:27:32,352
Where did you go to school?

325
00:27:32,486 --> 00:27:35,189
It was... It was called George Washington.

326
00:27:35,189 --> 00:27:39,026
Oh, GW? My brother-in-law
got his doctorate there.

327
00:27:40,928 --> 00:27:43,530
- Did you pledge?
- Yes.

328
00:27:43,530 --> 00:27:45,933
Every morning.

329
00:27:46,733 --> 00:27:50,704
It happened again!
David, the girl is absolutely useless.

330
00:27:50,838 --> 00:27:53,540
I need someone
who knows what she is doing.

331
00:27:53,640 --> 00:27:56,977
Excuse me. I'm not getting my mail.
Nothing has been filed.

332
00:27:57,110 --> 00:28:00,414
Ever since she got engaged,
my life has been a disaster.

333
00:28:00,414 --> 00:28:02,716
She came so highly recommended.

334
00:28:02,716 --> 00:28:05,652
She spent three months
writing down her married name.

335
00:28:05,719 --> 00:28:07,955
Mrs Judy Hicks. Mrs Donald Hicks.

336
00:28:07,955 --> 00:28:12,125
Mrs Judy Mitchelson Hicks - sometimes
with a hyphen, sometimes without.

337
00:28:12,192 --> 00:28:15,662
- Sometimes she spells the hyphen!
 -(snorts)

338
00:28:15,729 --> 00:28:19,700
- Well, I really don't know where I can put her.
- Put her on unemployment!

339
00:28:23,170 --> 00:28:26,507
- When can you start?
- Soon.

340
00:28:37,851 --> 00:28:40,988
We'll start you off
with last week's preschool orders.

341
00:28:41,088 --> 00:28:44,925
lt should take a few days -
give you a chance to find your way around.

342
00:28:45,058 --> 00:28:47,761
- Do you smoke?
- Well, just, uh... once. But...

343
00:28:47,761 --> 00:28:50,564
Only on breaks, and in the coffee room.

344
00:28:50,697 --> 00:28:54,535
Most of that's pretty straightforward stuff.
Any questions, come to me.

345
00:28:54,635 --> 00:28:56,937
Good luck!

346
00:28:59,439 --> 00:29:01,542
Bye!

347
00:29:13,520 --> 00:29:15,589
"The Dinky Link."

348
00:29:16,623 --> 00:29:19,059
"Seven."

349
00:29:19,359 --> 00:29:22,663
- "Jimmy's Toy Box."
- Psst!

350
00:29:23,096 --> 00:29:25,799
- "Squirmey Hermey."
- Psst!

351
00:29:26,633 --> 00:29:29,670
(clears throat)
Hey. Psst. Hey!

352
00:29:30,304 --> 00:29:34,675
- I'm Scott Brennen.
- Uh, I'm... I'm Josh Baskin.

353
00:29:34,675 --> 00:29:36,977
What are you trying to do?
Get us all fired?

354
00:29:37,077 --> 00:29:40,614
- Huh?
- You gotta slow down, pace yourself. Slowly.

355
00:29:40,747 --> 00:29:43,650
- Slow.
- Sorry.

356
00:29:43,750 --> 00:29:46,987
- Today's my first day.
- I know!

357
00:29:50,958 --> 00:29:53,560
- So how long have you worked here?
- Five years.

358
00:29:55,329 --> 00:29:58,565
The work stinks,
but the fringe benefits are great.

359
00:30:00,567 --> 00:30:02,836
See that girl over there in the red?

360
00:30:03,270 --> 00:30:05,973
Say hi to her and she's yours.

361
00:30:06,406 --> 00:30:10,844
She'll wrap her legs round you so tight,
you'll be begging for mercy.

362
00:30:10,978 --> 00:30:13,780
Well, I'll stay away from her, then!

363
00:30:15,015 --> 00:30:17,851
(phone rings)

364
00:30:17,951 --> 00:30:20,020
Excuse me.

365
00:30:20,153 --> 00:30:21,421
Brennen.

366
00:30:21,421 --> 00:30:24,191
I gave it to you yesterday! Oh, here it is.

367
00:30:25,259 --> 00:30:27,861
I don't have time to Xerox it.
Let the new guy do it.

368
00:30:27,861 --> 00:30:30,797
- Bullshit!
- But the favourability ratings...

369
00:30:30,864 --> 00:30:34,635
Let's not lie to ourselves.
If a kid likes a toy, it sells, that's all.

370
00:30:34,735 --> 00:30:39,973
- But every bit of research...
- It worked in the research, not with the kids!

371
00:30:41,842 --> 00:30:43,810
- Sorry.
- Watch where you're going!

372
00:30:43,911 --> 00:30:46,213
- Are you OK?
- I am fine.

373
00:30:46,313 --> 00:30:49,216
- You could kill somebody!
-(boss) It's all right.

374
00:30:49,349 --> 00:30:52,753
The boss should get
knocked on his ass once in a while.

375
00:30:52,886 --> 00:30:56,924
- Maybe you should see a doctor.
- For crying out loud, Paul, I'm fine!

376
00:30:57,057 --> 00:30:59,560
- Sorry, sir.
- Where were you going, son?

377
00:30:59,660 --> 00:31:05,899
Um... I was, uh... I was going to the Xerox
room cos they needed these by five o'clock.

378
00:31:06,033 --> 00:31:07,901
Oh! That's good!

379
00:31:08,001 --> 00:31:11,738
Nothing wrong with a little hustle.
Nothing at all.

380
00:31:12,906 --> 00:31:15,209
Right, Paul?

381
00:31:19,179 --> 00:31:21,348
What did he mean?
I hustle.

382
00:31:21,481 --> 00:31:23,550
Uh, sir? Sir!

383
00:31:29,389 --> 00:31:31,491
(phone rings)

384
00:31:32,926 --> 00:31:35,028
Hello?

385
00:31:35,529 --> 00:31:37,598
Uh...

386
00:31:39,399 --> 00:31:41,969
- Hello?
 -Hello.

387
00:31:42,102 --> 00:31:45,239
- Mrs Baskin?
- Yes?

388
00:31:46,507 --> 00:31:49,610
- How are you?
- Who is this?

389
00:31:50,878 --> 00:31:56,283
I just wanted you to know that, uh... Josh
is all right. I mean, he's OK and everything.

390
00:31:56,283 --> 00:31:58,385
Do you have my boy?

391
00:31:58,452 --> 00:32:01,522
Yeah... And you're gonna get him back -
just the way he was.

392
00:32:01,588 --> 00:32:07,427
Look, I swear to God, if you do anything
to him, if you touch one hair on his head,...

393
00:32:07,561 --> 00:32:10,764
..l will spend the rest of my life
making sure you suffer.

394
00:32:12,132 --> 00:32:14,234
Wow! Thanks.

395
00:32:15,068 --> 00:32:18,605
- Let me talk to Josh.
- Oh, he can't come to the phone right now.

396
00:32:18,705 --> 00:32:23,177
- Why not? What did you do to him?
- I-I didn't do anything. He's a terrific kid.

397
00:32:23,177 --> 00:32:26,547
(tearful) I want proof that he's all right.

398
00:32:26,613 --> 00:32:28,415
Uh... all right.

399
00:32:28,482 --> 00:32:33,620
Um... ask me something that...
that... that only he would know.

400
00:32:33,720 --> 00:32:37,024
Then I'll ask him for you,
and that way, you'll know that he's OK.

401
00:32:37,157 --> 00:32:40,093
Ask him what I used to sing to him
when he was a little boy.

402
00:32:43,297 --> 00:32:47,801
- Is there anything else you'd rather ask him?
- Ask him.

403
00:32:54,474 --> 00:32:56,777
I got it! I got it.

404
00:33:01,215 --> 00:33:03,851
(out of tune)
Memories

405
00:33:05,118 --> 00:33:07,621
Like the corner of my mind

406
00:33:07,688 --> 00:33:11,458
Misty, watercolour memories

407
00:33:11,592 --> 00:33:13,961
Of the way we were

408
00:33:14,695 --> 00:33:17,297
Scattered pictures

409
00:33:17,397 --> 00:33:18,465
Oh...

410
00:33:20,334 --> 00:33:22,836
Look, you're gonna see him again -
really soon.

411
00:33:22,936 --> 00:33:26,173
I-I promise. I... cross my heart and hope to...

412
00:33:26,807 --> 00:33:29,510
Uh... we'll talk about this later.

413
00:33:38,252 --> 00:33:40,220
(gunshots)

414
00:33:41,688 --> 00:33:43,790
(screaming)

415
00:33:53,567 --> 00:33:56,270
Get down! Get down! Get out of the area!

416
00:33:56,403 --> 00:33:58,505
(gunshot in street)

417
00:33:58,505 --> 00:34:00,574
(screaming)

418
00:34:00,674 --> 00:34:02,743
(sirens and gunshot)

419
00:34:05,379 --> 00:34:07,681
- Ferris.
- Thank you.

420
00:34:07,748 --> 00:34:10,184
Brennen.

421
00:34:10,250 --> 00:34:12,886
Baskin.

422
00:34:12,986 --> 00:34:15,055
- What is this?
- Payday.

423
00:34:15,189 --> 00:34:19,359
- (man) Hey, whoa! Where's mine?
- $187?

424
00:34:19,426 --> 00:34:21,028
- Yep.
- Oh! Oh!

425
00:34:21,094 --> 00:34:24,131
They really screw you, don't they?

426
00:34:26,033 --> 00:34:28,302
- Hi.
- Hi.

427
00:34:33,207 --> 00:34:35,709
OK... So how would you like that?

428
00:34:47,788 --> 00:34:50,224
OK. All right.

429
00:34:50,290 --> 00:34:53,126
Three dimes, a $100 bill, and 87 ones.

430
00:35:02,402 --> 00:35:04,805
One, two, three...

431
00:35:04,805 --> 00:35:06,573
More, more, more

432
00:35:06,974 --> 00:35:08,642
More, more, more!

433
00:35:13,881 --> 00:35:18,151
She don't like slavery
She won't sit and beg

434
00:35:22,222 --> 00:35:24,491
I'm never eating again.

435
00:35:26,093 --> 00:35:30,264
- It wasn't that bad.
- It was the boat ride that did it.

436
00:35:30,330 --> 00:35:32,766
No. It was the pork rinds.

437
00:35:32,966 --> 00:35:35,269
Pork rinds! Argh!

438
00:35:36,603 --> 00:35:38,672
Achoo!

439
00:35:38,906 --> 00:35:42,843
- We sure had fun, didn't we?
- Yeah. Yeah, we sure did.

440
00:35:43,177 --> 00:35:44,311
A...

441
00:35:45,913 --> 00:35:48,081
Booger! Booger!

442
00:36:07,801 --> 00:36:09,469
Welcome to our world
Welcome to our world

443
00:36:09,736 --> 00:36:12,039
Welcome to our world
Welcome to our world

444
00:36:12,172 --> 00:36:17,377
Welcome to our world of toys!

445
00:36:17,678 --> 00:36:19,146
Yee-hah!

446
00:36:19,279 --> 00:36:21,982
Oh! Keep away from strange men.

447
00:36:24,151 --> 00:36:26,220
(boy)
Gotcha!

448
00:36:26,353 --> 00:36:28,322
- What's your name?
- Joey. What's yours?

449
00:36:28,422 --> 00:36:31,024
- My name's Josh.
- I'm gonna blow you away, Josh.

450
00:36:31,158 --> 00:36:35,329
- I just got you!
- No way! That's bullshit. Get back here!

451
00:36:47,608 --> 00:36:50,544
(old woman)
You big dork!

452
00:36:54,915 --> 00:36:57,317
(electronic bleeping)

453
00:37:04,324 --> 00:37:07,227
You work for me, don't you?

454
00:37:07,327 --> 00:37:08,462
Yes.

455
00:37:08,462 --> 00:37:12,099
I thought so.
What? Are you here with your kids?

456
00:37:12,432 --> 00:37:14,535
No...

457
00:37:17,871 --> 00:37:21,008
- Uh, I was just looking around.
- Oh...

458
00:37:22,342 --> 00:37:25,379
Me, too. I come here every Saturday.

459
00:37:27,247 --> 00:37:30,250
You can't see this on a marketing report.

460
00:37:31,618 --> 00:37:34,221
What's a marketing report?

461
00:37:36,423 --> 00:37:38,525
Exactly.

462
00:37:38,592 --> 00:37:40,794
Come on.

463
00:37:42,563 --> 00:37:45,899
- What do you think of that?
- The championship hockey?

464
00:37:45,999 --> 00:37:48,535
- Yeah.
- Ooh, I love it. Only, the....

465
00:37:48,602 --> 00:37:52,906
- Only, what?
- Well, the pieces don't move.

466
00:37:52,973 --> 00:37:55,609
- What do you mean?
- Well, on the old set,...

467
00:37:55,609 --> 00:37:59,980
..you could slide the men up and down
the ice. Now all they do is spin around.

468
00:38:00,080 --> 00:38:03,550
It was more like real hockey the old way.
Why'd they change it?

469
00:38:03,550 --> 00:38:05,419
I don't know.

470
00:38:05,485 --> 00:38:09,022
The Starfighters are good -
you can change all the pieces around.

471
00:38:09,156 --> 00:38:11,258
But I never liked the Galacticons.

472
00:38:11,325 --> 00:38:13,827
You only get one robot,
and there's no vehicle.

473
00:38:13,961 --> 00:38:16,663
- Mm-hm. I see.
- Plus, you can't take 'em underwater.

474
00:38:16,763 --> 00:38:19,800
- And if you do, they...
- (musical note)

475
00:38:23,637 --> 00:38:25,305
Neat!

476
00:38:36,583 --> 00:38:38,852
OK, uh... let's check out the...

477
00:38:43,790 --> 00:38:46,894
("Heart and Soul")

478
00:38:50,464 --> 00:38:53,667
- Piano lessons?
