01:18:39,920 --> 01:18:42,222
If... If it's something else...

957
01:18:46,059 --> 01:18:51,398
Not that we have to know right now. But if we
think that it could turn into something else,...

958
01:18:51,465 --> 01:18:53,700
..well...

959
01:18:58,272 --> 01:19:01,208
How do you feel about all this?

960
01:19:02,242 --> 01:19:04,545
How do I feel about what?

961
01:19:07,247 --> 01:19:10,050
Well, how do... how do you... feel about me?

962
01:19:21,094 --> 01:19:24,364
(Josh fiddles with papers)

963
01:19:25,666 --> 01:19:28,602
What... What is that supposed to mean?

964
01:19:38,545 --> 01:19:40,814
(Susan)
Agh!

965
01:19:52,292 --> 01:19:54,661
Wednesday would be better than Thursday.

966
01:19:54,795 --> 01:19:58,232
- Mr Baskin can't be...
- Yeah, I have the key example right here.

967
01:19:58,966 --> 01:20:01,668
Where you been? I've been
trying to reach you!

968
01:20:01,768 --> 01:20:04,805
- I'm... I'm in the middle of something, OK?
- I got the list.

969
01:20:04,872 --> 01:20:10,010
- Can you give me a minute, please? Yes.
- What? This is it. This is the list!

970
01:20:10,110 --> 01:20:13,580
Would you come back at lunch?
I'm a little bit busy right now.

971
01:20:13,647 --> 01:20:15,015
- Hello?
- Busy?

972
01:20:15,015 --> 01:20:17,117
- Billy!
- Are you outta your mind?

973
01:20:17,184 --> 01:20:21,688
- Jesus, Billy! Miss Patterson!
- It's what we've been waiting for!

974
01:20:21,788 --> 01:20:25,726
I got work to do, can't you understand that?
I got a deadline to meet. God!

975
01:20:42,709 --> 01:20:46,580
I'm your best friend.
What's more important than that, huh?

976
01:20:49,917 --> 01:20:53,887
And I'm three months older
than you are, asshole!

977
01:21:38,999 --> 01:21:42,669
"You are standing in the cavern
of the evil wizard."

978
01:21:42,669 --> 01:21:46,840
"All around you are
the carcasses of slain ice dwarfs."

979
01:21:50,277 --> 01:21:52,679
"Melt wizard."

980
01:21:56,850 --> 01:21:59,653
"What do you want to melt him with?"

981
01:22:08,328 --> 01:22:11,031
"Throw thermal pod."

982
01:22:14,668 --> 01:22:16,970
Race you!

983
01:22:17,104 --> 01:22:19,173
Come on!

984
01:22:48,035 --> 01:22:52,539
-(woman) Boys! Time for dinner!
-(boy) Just five more minutes.

985
01:23:57,404 --> 01:23:59,773
Josh? What's wrong?

986
01:24:04,678 --> 01:24:06,847
What is it?

987
01:24:11,385 --> 01:24:15,556
I haven't told you something
because I didn't think you'd believe me,...

988
01:24:15,622 --> 01:24:18,258
..and I didn't think
you'd like me any more, so...

989
01:24:18,325 --> 01:24:22,930
Oh, honey, come here!
You can tell me anything. What?

990
01:24:28,869 --> 01:24:31,471
Susan, I'm not what you think I am.

991
01:24:33,974 --> 01:24:35,843
What do you mean?

992
01:24:37,311 --> 01:24:39,947
Before I met you, I was in Little League.

993
01:24:41,048 --> 01:24:43,050
Um... I was in Little League,...

994
01:24:43,050 --> 01:24:47,254
..and I rode my bike to school,
and I played with my friends and hung out...

995
01:24:47,254 --> 01:24:50,991
Jo... Josh, what are...
what are you talking about?

996
01:24:53,060 --> 01:24:55,462
I wanna go home.

997
01:24:57,231 --> 01:25:00,033
I miss my family, Susan,
and I wanna go home.

998
01:25:00,167 --> 01:25:02,870
Oh, my God! You're married!

999
01:25:03,303 --> 01:25:06,507
- No! No... I'm not married.
- I knew this was too good to be true.

1000
01:25:06,640 --> 01:25:10,611
- There had to be something!
- S... Susan, I'm not married.

1001
01:25:10,677 --> 01:25:12,779
- You're not?
- No.

1002
01:25:13,080 --> 01:25:16,016
I'm a child.

1003
01:25:16,083 --> 01:25:18,385
What?

1004
01:25:18,519 --> 01:25:23,924
I'm a child, Susan. And I...
I'm... I'm not ready for all of this!

1005
01:25:24,558 --> 01:25:28,729
Oh, that's fine. That is... That's just great(!)

1006
01:25:28,729 --> 01:25:30,831
- What happened...
- No, I understand.

1007
01:25:30,898 --> 01:25:35,269
- "I'm not ready to make a commitment."
- No! No, you don't understand.

1008
01:25:35,402 --> 01:25:38,338
- I... I'm 13 years old.
- Oh, and who isn't?

1009
01:25:38,405 --> 01:25:41,241
You think there isn't
a frightened kid inside of me?

1010
01:25:41,341 --> 01:25:44,178
No, I mean I really am thirteen!

1011
01:25:44,244 --> 01:25:49,383
I went to bed one night and I was a kid,
and when I woke up, I was a grown-up.

1012
01:25:49,483 --> 01:25:53,754
Oh, right(!) And just yesterday,
I was a schoolgirl with pigtails(!)

1013
01:25:53,854 --> 01:25:56,490
- Why are you doing this?
- There was a carnival...

1014
01:25:56,557 --> 01:25:59,693
- Please!
- I made a wish on the Zoltar machine.

1015
01:25:59,826 --> 01:26:01,361
Oh, stop it!

1016
01:26:01,495 --> 01:26:05,532
The Zoltar machine had this bobbing head
that looked just like a devil!

1017
01:26:05,666 --> 01:26:10,037
If you got a quarter in his mouth, you could
make a wish. I did! I made a wish to be big.

1018
01:26:10,103 --> 01:26:14,508
What I'm trying to tell you is, I changed
into a grown-up, but I'm really just a kid!

1019
01:26:14,608 --> 01:26:17,311
Fine, Josh. You're a kid.

1020
01:26:20,113 --> 01:26:23,383
Look, I don't know what it is
that you're trying to tell me,...

1021
01:26:23,450 --> 01:26:28,889
..but we have a very big presentation to give
tomorrow, so I'm gonna get some sleep.

1022
01:26:31,158 --> 01:26:33,594
(door slams)

1023
01:26:35,329 --> 01:26:38,265
Stupid stuff! Dumb stuff!

1024
01:26:38,398 --> 01:26:40,901
Some friend! I don't need him.

1025
01:26:45,072 --> 01:26:47,341
Stupid jacket!

1026
01:26:49,309 --> 01:26:51,945
(walkie-talkie crackles)

1027
01:26:52,145 --> 01:26:54,248
Josh?

1028
01:26:58,185 --> 01:27:00,287
Josh!

1029
01:27:03,824 --> 01:27:06,560
Oh... Hi, Mrs Baskin.

1030
01:27:17,471 --> 01:27:19,573
Hiya.

1031
01:27:19,673 --> 01:27:22,609
I was just looking around in here.

1032
01:27:22,609 --> 01:27:24,978
(Billy)
Hm.

1033
01:27:25,112 --> 01:27:28,515
- Your hair's getting longer.
- I got it cut yesterday.

1034
01:27:28,949 --> 01:27:31,018
Oh.

1035
01:27:33,954 --> 01:27:36,023
He had a birthday.

1036
01:27:36,590 --> 01:27:38,859
I... I know.

1037
01:27:40,961 --> 01:27:43,463
He'll be coming back real soon.

1038
01:27:46,166 --> 01:27:48,969
Everything's gonna be OK.

1039
01:27:51,038 --> 01:27:54,308
- I hope so.
- Good night.

1040
01:28:25,239 --> 01:28:27,541
(door opens)

1041
01:28:30,577 --> 01:28:33,514
Right there! Sea Point Park, New York.

1042
01:28:38,519 --> 01:28:40,821
Well?

1043
01:28:40,888 --> 01:28:43,190
(intercom buzzes)

1044
01:28:43,290 --> 01:28:46,527
- Yes?
- (Miss Patterson) They're waiting for you.

1045
01:28:53,934 --> 01:28:55,702
Thanks.

1046
01:28:55,836 --> 01:28:58,205
See you around.

1047
01:29:07,381 --> 01:29:11,051
There's this flat screen on the inside
with pictures on it.

1048
01:29:11,118 --> 01:29:15,022
You read it, and when you get to the bottom,
you have to make a choice...

1049
01:29:15,088 --> 01:29:20,427
..of what the character's gonna do - if he's
gonna fight the dragon, you push a button.

1050
01:29:23,430 --> 01:29:26,667
- Paul?
- I don't get it.

1051
01:29:26,967 --> 01:29:28,635
- Well...
-(Mac) Paul!

1052
01:29:28,869 --> 01:29:32,739
- It's a comic book...
- See, there's a computer chip inside,...

1053
01:29:32,806 --> 01:29:38,045
..which stores the choices. At the end
of a page, you decide where the story goes.

1054
01:29:38,145 --> 01:29:40,447
- That's the point.
- Terrific, Susan.

1055
01:29:41,148 --> 01:29:44,484
-(Susan) The kid makes his own decision.
-(Mac) This is possible?

1056
01:29:44,618 --> 01:29:47,321
Yeah! In  fact, it's a very simple program.

1057
01:29:48,155 --> 01:29:50,657
Isn't that... Isn't that right?

1058
01:29:51,792 --> 01:29:55,262
(Paul) So what happens
when you run out of choices?

1059
01:29:55,329 --> 01:29:58,999
(Susan) That's the great thing.
You can sell different adventures.

1060
01:29:59,099 --> 01:30:02,769
Just pop in a brand-new disk,
and you get a whole new set of options.

1061
01:30:02,836 --> 01:30:06,707
- We could market this on a comic-book rack.
-(Susan) Mm-hm.

1062
01:30:07,341 --> 01:30:09,443
I'll be right back.

1063
01:30:09,443 --> 01:30:12,012
(Mac)
How much would the unit cost?

1064
01:30:12,145 --> 01:30:16,116
Well, our initial figure
was around, uh... seven...

1065
01:30:18,285 --> 01:30:20,354
..around seven dollars,...

1066
01:30:20,487 --> 01:30:26,193
..with a retail cost of about... 18.95.

1067
01:30:28,095 --> 01:30:31,732
Well, you expect a kid
to pay $19 for a comic book?

1068
01:30:31,832 --> 01:30:34,268
I think a kid...

1069
01:30:40,908 --> 01:30:43,443
Will you excuse me?

1070
01:30:50,317 --> 01:30:52,386
Josh?

1071
01:30:52,486 --> 01:30:54,555
Josh!

1072
01:31:03,330 --> 01:31:05,399
(whistles)

1073
01:31:09,069 --> 01:31:11,872
Will you take me
to Sea Point Park, New York?

1074
01:31:12,005 --> 01:31:14,575
Sea Point Park? Josh!

1075
01:31:14,708 --> 01:31:16,376
- Not so fast!
- Here.

1076
01:31:16,376 --> 01:31:19,379
Josh! Josh!

1077
01:31:20,147 --> 01:31:22,716
See you back home!

1078
01:31:22,850 --> 01:31:25,152
Yeah!

1079
01:31:25,219 --> 01:31:28,055
Excuse me. Uh... do you know him?
You know Josh?

1080
01:31:28,055 --> 01:31:31,792
- Yeah... Yeah.
- Look, you have to tell me where he went.

1081
01:31:31,892 --> 01:31:34,528
- Who are you?
- I'm...

1082
01:31:36,063 --> 01:31:41,068
- I'm his girlfriend.
- Euch! (chuckles)

1083
01:31:41,502 --> 01:31:45,172
- Billy Kopeche.
- You have to tell me where he went.

1084
01:31:45,772 --> 01:31:47,875
Please, tell me.

1085
01:31:47,875 --> 01:31:50,177
Tell me!

1086
01:33:46,627 --> 01:33:48,896
Work, damn it!

1087
01:34:21,962 --> 01:34:24,264
- Josh?
- Susan!

1088
01:34:24,364 --> 01:34:27,401
You know, you don't walk out on somebody.

1089
01:34:28,435 --> 01:34:32,906
You don't just get up and leave and...
and walk out like that. You don't do that!

1090
01:34:33,040 --> 01:34:35,409
I know. I know. I'm really sorry.

1091
01:34:36,376 --> 01:34:39,980
I'm really sorry, but...
I didn't know what to do. I...

1092
01:34:40,113 --> 01:34:43,050
I didn't know what to say.

1093
01:35:01,602 --> 01:35:03,971
Oh, God!

1094
01:35:04,104 --> 01:35:06,406
You got your wish.

1095
01:35:07,441 --> 01:35:10,010
- I tried to tell you...
- I didn't listen.

1096
01:35:10,143 --> 01:35:12,880
- I guess I didn't hear you,...
- I tried to tell you.

1097
01:35:12,880 --> 01:35:19,186
- ..or want to! Even if I did listen...
- I've been thinking about this. I've been...

1098
01:35:20,153 --> 01:35:25,459
There's a million reasons for me to go home,
but there's only one reason for me to stay.

1099
01:35:27,895 --> 01:35:30,797
What... What reason is that?

1100
01:35:32,666 --> 01:35:34,768
Well...

1101
01:35:34,835 --> 01:35:36,937
..you!

1102
01:35:37,905 --> 01:35:41,008
Oh, come on... Come on. Come on, come on!

1103
01:35:48,315 --> 01:35:51,118
So, uh... what are you? Fifteen? Sixteen?

1104
01:35:53,754 --> 01:35:56,657
Well... I'm thirteen.

1105
01:35:56,657 --> 01:35:58,759
Ohh...

1106
01:36:02,696 --> 01:36:04,998
Well, that explains it!

1107
01:36:16,677 --> 01:36:19,246
Maybe you could come with me.

1108
01:36:22,316 --> 01:36:24,818
No! Ha!

1109
01:36:24,885 --> 01:36:26,253
No...

1110
01:36:26,253 --> 01:36:28,355
Why not?

1111
01:36:28,422 --> 01:36:31,158
I've... I've been there before.

1112
01:36:35,028 --> 01:36:37,598
It's hard enough the first time.

1113
01:36:38,999 --> 01:36:41,502
You know what I mean?

1114
01:36:42,736 --> 01:36:45,339
You don't know what I mean.

1115
01:36:54,281 --> 01:36:57,150
Come on, I'll drive you home.

1116
01:37:02,022 --> 01:37:05,459
- I'm sorry.
- No, I'll be OK.

1117
01:37:05,559 --> 01:37:07,761
You'll be fine.

1118
01:37:07,861 --> 01:37:10,364
In ten years, who knows?

1119
01:37:11,932 --> 01:37:14,868
Maybe you should hold onto my number.

1120
01:37:33,220 --> 01:37:35,789
So this is where you live?

1121
01:37:37,257 --> 01:37:41,028
- Which one is it?
- That one right there, just...

1122
01:37:41,128 --> 01:37:44,064
(Susan)
Oh. That's nice.

1123
01:37:48,735 --> 01:37:51,772
I'm gonna miss you.

1124
01:37:51,772 --> 01:37:54,474
I'm gonna miss you, too.

1125
01:37:58,245 --> 01:38:01,782
- You won't even remember me.
- Oh, yes, I will.

1126
01:40:06,073 --> 01:40:08,175
Mom?

1127
01:40:08,976 --> 01:40:11,078
- Mom!
- Josh?

1128
01:40:11,078 --> 01:40:13,180
- It's me!
- Josh?

1129
01:40:13,981 --> 01:40:16,517
Josh! Oh, my God!

1130
01:40:16,583 --> 01:40:18,652
Oh, thank God you're home!

1131
01:40:18,785 --> 01:40:21,922
Oh, Mom... I missed you all so much.

1132
01:40:31,732 --> 01:40:35,068
-(Josh) I'm just not good enough.
- What are you talking about?

1133
01:40:35,068 --> 01:40:38,405
You hit the ball over the fence
almost every time in stickball.

1134
01:40:38,472 --> 01:40:42,142
- You just gotta get used to a fatter bat.
- (both chuckle)

1135
01:40:43,210 --> 01:40:45,579
-(Josh) You really think I could do it?
- Yeah!

1136
01:40:45,679 --> 01:40:50,284
- (Josh) Come on, we'll hit some after supper.
- OK. I'll call for ya.

